---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Sunrise Family Farms — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="After 250% growth in a single year, Sunrise Family Farms automated the manual palletizing line that had become its bottleneck — so tradition could scale without breaking its people."
  ogTitle="Sunrise Family Farms — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="250% growth in a year · zero capital · tradition, scaled smarter"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/sunrise-family-farms" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Sunrise Family Farms
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Sunrise Family Farms</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">How Sunrise Family Farms Is Using Automation to Preserve Tradition and Scale Smarter</h1>
    <p class="lede">After 250% growth in a single year, Sunrise Family Farms — a 25-year-old Norwich, NY creamery — automated the manual palletizing line that had become its bottleneck, so tradition could scale without breaking its people.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/sunrise-family-farms-hero.jpg" alt="Sunrise Family Farms creamery production" />
      <span class="dv-cap">Sunrise Family Farms · Norwich, NY</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">In business</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">25+ years</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Location</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Norwich, NY</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Dairy / creamery</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Products</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Yogurt, kefir, buttermilk</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Growth</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">250% in a year</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Tradition, <em>meet the bottleneck</em>.</h2>
      <p>Sunrise had already automated bottle handling and its bulk filling line — so manual palletizing, running three shifts six days a week of constant bending, lifting, and twisting, became the bottleneck. With 250% growth in the last year and new contracts requiring more output, the manual process was hindering the creamery's ability to scale. Co-owner Charlie Reinshagen put it plainly: he wouldn't retire until a robot was in.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Bottle handling and bulk filling already automated</li>
        <li>Palletizing: 3 shifts, 6 days a week of strain</li>
        <li>250% growth in a single year</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Robotic palletizer taking on the manual stacking task" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Manual palletizing · automated</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Formic Full Service palletizing system" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Start small · dream big</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>Start small, <em>dream big</em>.</h2>
      <p>Management built buy-in from the floor first — asking the team where automation could remove bottlenecks — then chose Formic's Full Service model: no upfront capital, ongoing technical support, built-in maintenance, and remote troubleshooting. With the heaviest task handled, employees could focus on more fulfilling, higher-impact work.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Floor-level buy-in before deployment</li>
        <li>Full Service: no capital, remote troubleshooting</li>
        <li>Employees freed for higher-value work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"Fully supported automation with no capital was ideal for us. You can buy an automation system, but you never know what tomorrow will bring. There is no risk for us with Formic. The service is there, and the reliability is there."</blockquote>
      <cite>Roland Klimm · Co-Owner, Sunrise Family Farms</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Preserve tradition. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Scale smarter.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">250%</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Growth in a year</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">25+</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Years of tradition</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">$0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Capital invested</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Scale without <em>losing what matters</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
